MCS vs. MSCS
Home>About>MCS vs. MSCS







Compare the MCS and MSCS degrees to see which one is right for you…




Master of Computer Science (MCS)
Master of Science in Computer Science (MSCS)


Focus


 This is a professional program designed for students interested in careers in high-tech industry, business and government related fields.




This is a Master of Science program designed for students interested in:

research
possible future PhD programs
careers in industry or academia






Dedicated Career Counselor


 Program offers a dedicated Career Counselor to help prepare students for the workforce




 Students have access to the UCI Career Center




Target Student Population


Students interested in professional preparation
Those drawn to a shorter time to degree




Research oriented students




Time to Degree


16 month program, Beginning of Fall quarter to end of Fall quarter




 5-6 quarters




Units


 48 units (11 courses) – see site for course descriptions




Minimum 47 units (14 courses)




Tuition


$45,000 (Regardless of residency)
https://mcs.ics.uci.edu/prospective-students/cost-and-financial-aid/




Resident: $5,660.5 per quarter
Non-Resident: $10,695 per quarter




Degree


Master of Computer Science




Master of Science




Fellowships


Up to 100% of tuition for domestic students based on academic merit
Up to 100% of tuition for diverse and underrepresented domestic students




Self-funded




Schedule


Classes and labs offered primarily in late afternoons and evenings




Classes and labs offered throughout day




Exit Exam


Capstones– Developing professional design and writing skills




 Thesis or comprehensive exam options




GRE required?


YES




YES




Letter of recommendations


Minimum 3




Minimum 3




TOEFL/ IELTS required?


International students – YES.
The minimum TOEFL score is 80. For more information, please see Graduate Division’s English Proficiency site.
UCI will only waive the TOEFL requirement for applicants who have completed ALL requirements for a B.S., M.S. or Ph.D. degree in the U.S. prior to submitting their application.
As an alternative to the TOEFL, you may submit scores from the Academic Modules of the International English Language Testing System (IELTS).UC Irvine only accepts scores submitted electronically by the IELTS test center. An overall score of 7 for admission, with a score of no less than 6 on any individual module.




International students – YES.
The minimum TOEFL score is 80. For more information, please see Graduate Division’s English Proficiency site.
UCI will only waive the TOEFL requirement for applicants who have completed ALL requirements for a B.S., M.S. or Ph.D. degree in the U.S. prior to submitting their application.
As an alternative to the TOEFL, you may submit scores from the Academic Modules of the International English Language Testing System (IELTS).UC Irvine only accepts scores submitted electronically by the IELTS test center. An overall score of 7 for admission, with a score of no less than 6 on any individual module.





 





































